HEADWORD: Manoeuvrer
<hw>Ma*noeu"vrer</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who maneuvers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This charming widow Beaumont is a <qex>nanoeuvrer</qex>. We can't
well make an English word of it.</q> <rj><qau>Miss
Edgeworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

